3.19 Invoice Submission and Payment

(a) Following AT&T's Acceptance of Location, the Vendor shall submit two identical invoices to AT&T for the applicable Cell Site. These invoices should reflect the terms outlined in the AT&T Purchase Order and clearly outline the Material, Deliverables, and Services provided for that specific Cell Site. The Vendor's invoice should specify, where applicable:

   (i) Quantities of each item of Material, Deliverable, and Service;
   (ii) Prices for each item of Material, Deliverable, and Service;
   (iii) Tax status and the tax amount per item, if applicable;
   (iv) Total amounts for each item;
   (v) Total amount of sales or use taxes;
   (vi) Any discounts applied;
   (vii) Shipping charges, if applicable;
   (viii) The total amount due;
   (ix) The remit to address;
   (x) Descriptions of Material, Deliverables, and Services;
   (xi) Special service charges, if any.

Each invoice should clearly state that payment will be made in accordance with the terms set out in this Agreement, and all payments for amounts due on such invoices for Material, Deliverables, and Services provided under the Build Addendum will follow the Structured Payments Schedule as outlined in Schedule 3 of the Build Addendum.

AT&T will review the invoice promptly, and unless AT&T disputes, in good faith, the amounts stated therein, AT&T will acknowledge that the payment structure set out in the invoice is due in accordance with this Agreement and the Build Addendum. If AT&T has any good faith disputes about the amounts listed on an invoice, it must provide written notice to the Vendor before the due date of the first Structured Payment specified in the invoice.

The Vendor will submit a payment request to AT&T on a monthly basis, on the first day of each calendar month, for the Structured Payments outlined in the Build Addendum and the Maintenance Fees outlined in the Maintenance Addendum. AT&T must pay the Vendor no later than sixty (60) days after receipt of such payment request for Structured Payments. For invoices related to Maintenance Fees, AT&T must either pay the Vendor or provide written notice of any good faith dispute within ninety (90) days of receiving the invoice. Any dispute about a Maintenance Fee invoice must be made in good faith and should detail the disputed amounts and the reason for the dispute. Despite any good faith dispute, AT&T will pay all undisputed amounts to the Vendor on or before the due date for that invoice.

Any invoices received by AT&T more than one (1) year after the Delivery of Materials and Deliverables, or the provision of Services, are considered late and AT&T has no obligation to pay such invoices.
